cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically ground segmentation in Velodyne point clouds using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which suggest the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely options. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics and autonomous systems, which suggest the category cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as a possible option. Finally, the paper involves training and evaluating CNNs, which suggest the category cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible option.
